          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1670343947398-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, drain and rinse your <strong>red kidney beans</strong></p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> sweet potato[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add your<strong> soy sauce</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> to 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>soy</strong> <strong>stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
